'''Nikken''' (日乾, 1560 - December 6, 1635) was a Buddhist monk of the [[:en:Nichiren-shū|Nichiren-shū]] sect active during the [[:en:Azuchi–Momoyama period|Azuchi–Momoyama period]] to the early [[:en:Edo period|Edo period]]. He was born in [[:en:Wakasa Province|Wakasa Province]] and had the Dharma name "Kōjun" (孝順). He also bore the title "Jakushō-in" (寂照院). Nikken gained the patronage of [[:en:Tokugawa Yorinobu|Tokugawa Yorinobu]], the lord of [[:en:Kii Province|Kii Province]]'s [[:en:Kishū Domain|Kishū Domain]]. With Yorinobu's support, Nikken played a significant role in the revival of [[Rennyō-ji Temple]] (蓮永寺) in [[:en:Suruga Province|Suruga Province]]. == See Also == * [[Jōshō-ji Temple (Kyoto)]] * [[Sadoga Hajime Hokke Honzon]] (佐渡始顕本尊)
